cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on sentence embedding. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new model that uses attention mechanisms, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the model uses a tree structure, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence and falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions using the model for image captioning, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper proposes a new training strategy, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
